data.meta_description:
81 likes, 0 comments - levenger on December 30, 2020: ""Happy birthday Rudyard Kipling. The English author and poet was born in India (1865), which inspired much of his writing. He is remembered as an innovator in the art of the ‘short story’, such as “The Jungle Book” (1894) and “Just So Stories” (1902). Notable poems include “If—”(1910)  and “Gunga Din” (1890). Kipling received the 1907 Nobel Prize in Literature.⁠
⁠
Do you have a favorite Kipling book?⁠
⁠
#RudyardKipling #IncredibleIndia #TheJungleBook #Levenger"".
